    "# 100. The Closed-Loop Network Design Problem\n",
    "## Tier 6: The Autonomous Self-Optimizing Ecosystem\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Assumptions\n",
    "- Distributed multi-agent system with autonomous decision making\n",
    "- Market mechanisms coordinate agent interactions and resource allocation\n",
    "- Contract Net Protocol enables efficient agent negotiations\n",
    "- Emergent intelligence arises from simple agent rules\n",
    "- Self-organizing network adapts to changing conditions\n",
    "- Decentralized control eliminates single points of failure\n",
    "\n",
    "### Approach (Step-by-Step)\n",
    "1. **Multi-Agent Architecture**: Design distributed agent system\n",
    "2. **Market Mechanisms**: Implement auction-based resource allocation\n",
    "3. **Contract Net Protocol**: Enable agent negotiations and agreements\n",
    "4. **Emergent Behavior**: Study system-level patterns from agent interactions\n",
    "5. **Self-Organization**: Enable autonomous network adaptation\n",
    "6. **Performance Optimization**: Monitor and improve ecosystem efficiency\n",
    "\n",
    "### What to Look for in Results\n",
    "- Multi-agent coordination and negotiation patterns\n",
    "- Market efficiency and resource allocation outcomes\n",
    "- Emergent system behavior and intelligence\n",
    "- Self-organization and adaptation capabilities\n",
    "- Network resilience and fault tolerance\n",
    "- Performance optimization and learning curves\n",
    "\n",
    "### Concrete Example\n",
    "We'll implement:\n",
    "- 20+ autonomous agents with different capabilities and objectives\n",
    "- Market-based auction system for resource allocation\n",
    "- Contract Net Protocol for agent negotiations\n",
    "- Self-organizing network with emergent intelligence\n",
    "- Performance monitoring and optimization"
   ]
